connecting with github actions, for auto deploy


1. Generate an SSH key for GitHub Actions

ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -C "github-action-deploy"
akses name and pass 


2. log into the ssh and add this key inside this file by doing
 nano ~/.ssh/authorized_keys


 3. go to github create repo secret in 
 repository → Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions → New repository secret

 Add the following:

Secret Name	Value
EC2_SSH_KEY	(Contents of your deploy_key private key file — the one without .pub)
EC2_HOST	13.62.176.157(AWS Public IP)
EC2_USER	ubuntu